85 // 1. Enable ENABLE_BISECT_TOOL below.
86 // 2. Make a new script `tmp.sh` calling a failing replay:
87 // python tests/run_replay_tests.py --filter stellar --frame 40000 --extra_args="-replay-fail-assert-instant -test-bisect $1"
88 // 3. Run the bisect script (may need to increase the end range up to 100000 or more):
89 // bash ~/tools/find-first-fail.sh -s 0 -e 10000 -v -q bash tmp.sh
90 // 4. For the number given, set `-test-bisect` to that, and set a breakpoint
